# Daily Log â€” Dec 27

## Focus

Custom VPC build with public/private subnets and NAT Gateway.

## Key Learnings

- VPC defines security boundaries
- Routing controls reachability
- NAT enables safe outbound access

## What Could Go Wrong?

- Exposing private subnets via IGW
- Misconfigured route tables
- Treating NAT as a firewall

## How to Defend

- Strict routing separation
- Least exposure
- Review routes regularly

## Tradeoffs

- NAT cost vs security
- Simplicity vs fine-grained control
